HEADWORD: Xanthium
<hw>Xan"thi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>xa`nqion</grk> a plant used for dyeing the hair yellow, said to be
the <spn>Xanthium strumarium</spn>, from <grk>xanqo`s</grk>
yellow.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of composite plants in
which the scales of the involucre are united so as to form a kind of
bur; cocklebur; clotbur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

